1
00:00:22,556 --> 00:00:24,723
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>I JUST WANNA KNOW WHO I AM.</i>     


2
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,227
<i>I CAN STAND ANYTHING</i>            
<i>FOR THAT.</i>                       


3
00:00:35,735 --> 00:00:37,702
<i>I'LL NEVER GIVE UP,</i>             
<i>SYDNEY, EVER.</i>                   


4
00:00:44,911 --> 00:00:49,581
IT'S BEEN THREE DAYS,           
JAROD, WITH TEMPERATURE         
OVER 100 DEGREES.               


5
00:00:49,650 --> 00:00:51,750
YOU DON'T HAVE TO               
GO ON, JAROD.                   


6
00:00:53,354 --> 00:00:55,621
                I CAN DO IT.    


7
00:00:55,689 --> 00:00:58,290
    I JUST WANNA KNOW WHO I AM. 


8
00:00:58,358 --> 00:01:00,359
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>I CAN STAND ANYTHING</i>            
<i>FOR THAT.</i>                       


9
00:01:00,427 --> 00:01:03,028
[ Beeping ]                     
WHERE DID THEY FIND THIS?       


10
00:01:03,097 --> 00:01:07,299
    CLEANUP CREW FOUND IT       
    IN A CABIN ABOUT 50 MILES   
    SOUTH OF ALBUQUERQUE.       


11
00:01:07,368 --> 00:01:09,334
            <i> [ Sydney ]</i>         
            <i> A GIFT FROM JAROD.</i> 
        HMM.                    


12
00:01:09,403 --> 00:01:11,336
SO, WHAT DOES IT MEAN?          


13
00:01:11,405 --> 00:01:15,140
I'M NOT SURE WHAT               
THE ORIGINAL INTENT             
OF THE SIMULATION WAS.          


14
00:01:15,209 --> 00:01:17,141
<i>I'LL HAVE TO RUN IT</i>             
<i>THROUGH THE ARCHIVES.</i>           


15
00:01:17,211 --> 00:01:19,544
<i>SAVE YOUR SWEAT.</i>                
<i>IT'S JUST ANOTHER DIVERSION.</i>    


16
00:01:19,613 --> 00:01:24,149
<i>I BEG TO DIFFER, MISS PARKER.</i>   
<i>THIS IS VERY IMPORTANT TO JAROD.</i>


17
00:01:24,218 --> 00:01:27,919
    HE'S REACHING OUT,          
    TAKING A LEAP OF FAITH.     


18
00:01:29,623 --> 00:01:32,724
<i>[ Jarod Shouting ]</i>              
<i>ALL RIGHT. NOW, REMEMBER WHAT</i>   
<i>YOU LEARNED IN CLASS.</i>           


19
00:01:32,793 --> 00:01:36,261
    I THINK I'M GONNA THROW UP! 
OH, NO, NO.                     
YOU'RE GONNA BE JUST FINE!      


20
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:39,498
        WELL, YOU'RE THE EXPERT.
    SORT OF.                    


21
00:01:39,566 --> 00:01:42,734
        SORT OF?                
        EXACTLY HOW MANY TIMES  
        HAVE YOU JUMPED?        


22
00:01:42,803 --> 00:01:45,103
COUNTING THIS?                  
                YES!            


23
00:01:45,172 --> 00:01:47,572
    ONE.                        


24
00:01:47,641 --> 00:01:49,641
    [ Woman Screaming ]         


25
00:01:50,644 --> 00:01:54,145
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


26
00:03:07,387 --> 00:03:09,688
                TOUGH JUMP?     


27
00:03:09,757 --> 00:03:11,990
    I MAY HAVE UNDERESTIMATED   
    MY PAYLOAD.                 


28
00:03:12,059 --> 00:03:15,727
        <i> WELL, THEY COME IN</i>     
        <i> ALL SHAPES AND SIZES.</i>  
        <i> RUB SOME OF THIS ON IT.</i>


29
00:03:16,963 --> 00:03:19,030
WHAT IS IT?                     
                HORSE LINIMENT. 


30
00:03:19,099 --> 00:03:22,567
    THEY USE IT ON THOROUGHBREDS
    WHEN THEY PULL A MUSCLE.    


31
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:24,569
    A FEW MORE OF THEM EL PASO  
    HOUSEWIVES,                 


32
00:03:24,638 --> 00:03:27,038
YOU'LL BE DRINKIN' THE STUFF.   


33
00:03:27,107 --> 00:03:29,708
            [ Sighs ] ANOTHER   
            SATISFIED CUSTOMER. 


34
00:03:29,776 --> 00:03:32,376
NICE TO SEE THAT YOU CAN CARRY  
YOUR WEIGHT AROUND HERE.        


35
00:03:32,445 --> 00:03:34,646
    THE INSTRUCTOR JOB IS YOURS 
    IF YOU STILL WANT IT.       


36
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:37,749
GREAT! IT'S A PLEASURE          
TO BE HERE.                     
                        GOOD.   


37
00:03:39,019 --> 00:03:42,086
CROCKETT. DID I GET A CALL      
FROM TASCO?                     


38
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:44,022
    <i> [ Crockett ]</i>               
    <i> PHONE HASN'T RUNG ALL DAY.</i> 


39
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:46,024
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>HOW'S THE OLD GIRL HOLDING UP?</i>  


40
00:03:46,092 --> 00:03:49,461
[ Scoffs ] I WAS ABLE TO PATCH  
THE LEAK IN THE FUEL PUMP,      


41
00:03:49,529 --> 00:03:51,496
            BUT SHE'S DEFINITELY
            ON DEATH'S DOOR.    


42
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:54,332
<i>JUST HOLD HER TOGETHER FOR A FEW</i>
<i>MORE DAYS...</i>                    


43
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:56,634
<i>AND I'LL HAVE THAT NEW PLANE</i>    
<i>FLOWN IN FROM PHOENIX.</i>          


44
00:04:01,808 --> 00:04:04,509
YOUR RÉSUMÉ IS VERY IMPRESSIVE. 


45
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:07,712
        82nd AIRBORNE,          
        ARMY RANGER.            


46
00:04:07,781 --> 00:04:12,116
<i>LOFTY CREDENTIALS FOR SOMEONE</i>   
<i>LOOKING TO TEACH THE PUBLIC</i>     
<i>TO TUCK AND ROLL.</i>               


47
00:04:12,185 --> 00:04:15,787
                        <i> WHY US?</i>
    WELL, I'M ON THE RUN        
    FROM A SECRET ORGANIZATION. 


48
00:04:15,855 --> 00:04:17,789
        I NEEDED A PLACE        
        TO HIDE OUT FOR A WHILE.


49
00:04:22,229 --> 00:04:26,364
<i>[ Broots ] WE'VE BEEN OVER THIS</i> 
<i>SIMULATION A DOZEN TIMES. I'M</i>   
<i>NOT SURE I UNDERSTAND THE POINT.</i>


50
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:31,370
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>SYDNEY DIDN'T ALWAYS</i>            
<i>HAVE METHOD, JUST MADNESS.</i>      


51
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:34,038
<i>IT WAS A PSYCHOLOGICAL STUDY</i>    
<i>TO DETERMINE...</i>                 


52
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:37,142
    IF THE MIND CAN ENABLE      
    THE BODY TO EXCEED          
    ITS NATURAL CAPABILITIES... 


53
00:04:37,211 --> 00:04:39,577
WHEN AN EMOTIONAL STIMULUS      
IS APPLIED.                     


54
00:04:39,646 --> 00:04:44,115
LIKE WHEN-- WHEN A CAR'S ON TOP 
OF A CHILD, AND THE MOTHER      
LIFTS IT OFF WITH ONE HAND.     


55
00:04:44,184 --> 00:04:45,750
            EXACTLY.            


56
00:04:45,819 --> 00:04:48,320
    <i> [ Man ] MISS PARKER, THIS</i>  
    <i> BIRTHDAY GIFT JUST ARRIVED.</i>


57
00:04:53,326 --> 00:04:55,427
        IS TODAY YOUR BIRTHDAY? 
        HOW OLD ARE YOU?        


58
00:04:56,896 --> 00:04:59,831
            OH. YOUNG, I'M SURE.


59
00:05:03,703 --> 00:05:05,637
                    JAROD.      


60
00:05:19,586 --> 00:05:21,352
            KNOW THIS MAN?      


61
00:05:21,421 --> 00:05:24,456
I'VE NEVER SEEN HIM BEFORE      
IN MY LIFE.                     


62
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:32,263
INTERESTING.                    


63
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:38,536
IT'S A DEAD FLOWER, SYDNEY,     
NOT THE SHROUD OF TURIN.        


64
00:05:38,605 --> 00:05:41,106
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>EXCUSE ME FOR SAYING THIS,</i>      


65
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:43,542
BUT IT DOESN'T EXACTLY LOOK LIKE
BUSINESS IS BOOMING.            


66
00:05:43,610 --> 00:05:45,810
WE'VE HAD SOME PROBLEMS,        
BUT THEY'RE ALL BEHIND US NOW.  


67
00:05:45,879 --> 00:05:47,812
                    PROBLEMS?   


68
00:05:47,881 --> 00:05:49,814
I LOST MY PARTNER A COUPLE      
OF MONTHS AGO.                  


69
00:05:49,883 --> 00:05:55,219
TOM MILES? I SAW THE PICTURE    
OF THE TWO OF YOU IN THE HANGAR.


70
00:05:55,288 --> 00:05:59,291
HE, UH, MADE A JUMP ABOUT       
200 MILES OUT INTO THE DESERT.  


71
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:04,161
TOM WAS ALWAYS TESTING HIMSELF. 
                    TESTING?    


72
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:08,834
HE TOOK ONE CANTEEN OF WATER,   
A COMPASS, AND A KNIFE,         
AND HIKED BACK IN.              


73
00:06:08,902 --> 00:06:12,204
IT WAS THIS...                  
YEARLY RITUAL.                  


74
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:17,708
UH, SOMETHING WENT WRONG        
AND... HE DIED.                 


75
00:06:19,813 --> 00:06:22,947
SO ALL I CAN DO NOW             
IS MAKE TOM'S DREAM...          


76
00:06:23,016 --> 00:06:28,920
OF TURNING BLUE DESERT          
INTO THE BEST SKYDIVING         
SCHOOL IN TEXAS COME TRUE.      


77
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:31,589
WE'RE GONNA GET A NEW           
JUMP PLANE, REDO THE HANGAR.    


78
00:06:31,658 --> 00:06:34,225
MAYBE EVEN BUILD A NEW          
INDOOR TRAINING FACILITY.       


79
00:06:34,294 --> 00:06:37,729
            HMM.                
TOM DESERVES THAT.              


80
00:06:37,798 --> 00:06:42,466
IT'S NOT MUCH TO LOOK AT,       
BUT, UH, THE A.C. WORKS.        
THERE'S A PHONE AND VCR.        


81
00:06:42,535 --> 00:06:45,103
<i>AND FOR THE MOST PART,</i>          
<i>IT KEEPS THE SNAKES OUT.</i>        


82
00:06:45,172 --> 00:06:47,738
        - WELL, I'M SURE        
          IT WILL BE FINE.      
        -<i> [ Horn Honks ]</i>        


83
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:54,879
WHAT ARE YOU DOING WAY OUT HERE 
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE DAY?       


84
00:06:54,948 --> 00:06:57,915
    WELL, I HAD SOME BUSINESS   
    OVER IN MASON COUNTY, SO... 


85
00:06:57,984 --> 00:07:00,585
<i>THOUGHT I MIGHT SEE IF</i>          
<i>YOU WANTED TO GET SOME LUNCH.</i>   


86
00:07:00,654 --> 00:07:03,188
        MEAT LOAF'S ON SPECIAL  
        AT THE DINER.           


87
00:07:03,257 --> 00:07:05,957
        UNLESS I'M INTERRUPTING 
        SOMETHING.              


88
00:07:06,026 --> 00:07:09,093
OH, JAROD COCHRAN, THIS IS,     
UH, SHERIFF DWIGHT KUNKLE.      


89
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:12,230
        - SHERIFF.              
        - MR. COCHRAN.          


90
00:07:12,298 --> 00:07:15,133
<i>JAROD HERE IS OUR LATEST</i>        
<i>ADDITION TO THE JUMP SCHOOL.</i>    


91
00:07:15,201 --> 00:07:16,735
            HUH. WHERE YOU FROM?


92
00:07:16,803 --> 00:07:20,037
OH, HERE AND THERE.             
WHICHEVER WAY THE WIND BLOWS.   


93
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,974
        HOW ABOUT THAT LUNCH?   


94
00:07:23,043 --> 00:07:24,976
WELL, I WAS JUST GONNA          
SHOW JAROD--                    
                    <i> OH, NO, NO.</i>


95
00:07:25,045 --> 00:07:27,879
    YOU TWO GO AHEAD.           
    I'LL BE JUST FINE.          
    NICE TO MEET YOU, SHERIFF.  


96
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,881
                    COCHRAN.    


97
00:07:32,386 --> 00:07:34,986
[ Starts Engine ]               


98
00:08:00,213 --> 00:08:02,146
                <i> [ Man ]</i>        
                <i> YOU'RE LATE.</i>   


99
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:04,315
    I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR YOU.  


100
00:08:04,384 --> 00:08:08,119
    - EXCUSE ME?                
    - I WAS TOLD A TRAVELER     
      WOULD COME SEEKING TRUTH. 


101
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:10,488
    - TOLD BY WHOM?             
    - THE SKY FATHERS.          


102
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:15,093
    <i> WHAT YOU WOULD CALL</i>        
    <i> A GUT FEELING. THEY SAID</i>   
    <i> YOU WOULD NEED A GUIDE.</i>    


103
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:16,861
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.             


104
00:08:16,930 --> 00:08:19,096
            SEE WHAT I MEAN?    


105
00:08:34,914 --> 00:08:36,848
    HOW'D HE DO THAT?           


106
00:08:36,917 --> 00:08:38,849
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>WELL?</i>                           


107
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,985
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>I RAN HIS PICTURE</i>               
<i>THROUGH THE SYSTEM.</i>             


108
00:08:41,054 --> 00:08:43,154
IF HE'S ANY KIND OF             
CENTRE CONTRACTOR,              


109
00:08:43,222 --> 00:08:45,389
THEN HE'S EITHER BEEN DELETED,  


110
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:47,892
OR HE'S OUT                     
OF OUR CLEARANCE LEVEL.         


111
00:08:47,961 --> 00:08:50,695
             NOBODY'S OUT OF    
            <i> MY</i> CLEARANCE LEVEL.


112
00:08:50,764 --> 00:08:53,998
            <i> WHAT ABOUT THIS?</i>   
    TORTURE.                    


113
00:08:54,067 --> 00:08:57,501
                    TORTURE?    
JAROD'S PLAYING GAMES.          


114
00:08:57,571 --> 00:09:01,105
                        WHY?    
BECAUSE HE WANTS TO             
GIVE ME AN ANEURYSM.            


115
00:09:01,174 --> 00:09:04,308
I DON'T KNOW WHY.               
IT'S... JUST                    
WHAT HE DOES.                   


116
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,310
    WHAT ABOUT THE PICTURE?     


117
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:08,346
I BLEW IT UP THREE              
WAYS FROM SUNDAY.               


118
00:09:08,415 --> 00:09:11,816
<i>SEE, LET ME SHOW YOU.</i>           
<i>ALL I GOT IS A STREET SIGN.</i>     


119
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:15,686
<i>BLACK RIDGE LANE.</i>               
<i>I DON'T KNOW IF THAT</i>            
<i>HELPS WITH ANYTHING.</i>            


120
00:09:15,755 --> 00:09:17,688
<i>MAYBE THE LOCATION.</i>             


121
00:09:17,757 --> 00:09:19,690
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT. MAYBE HE    
JUST WANTS TO TORTURE YOU.      


122
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:21,525
                BROOTS.         
    WHAT?                       


123
00:09:21,594 --> 00:09:23,527
                ZOOM IN ON THAT.
    WHAT?                       


124
00:09:23,596 --> 00:09:26,530
            <i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>    
            <i> THE REFLECTION</i>     
            <i> ON THE WINDSHIELD.</i> 


125
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:29,667
    <i> [ Keyboarding ]</i>            


126
00:09:29,735 --> 00:09:31,903
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>AGAIN.</i>                          


127
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:34,372
<i>AGAIN.</i>                          


128
00:09:34,441 --> 00:09:37,041
<i>ONE MORE TIME, SHARPER.</i>         
[ Computer Beeping ]            


129
00:09:40,647 --> 00:09:43,214
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>MAINE.</i>                          


130
00:09:43,283 --> 00:09:45,416
I'LL BE DAMNED!                 


131
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:51,622
<i>[ Vehicle Approaching ]</i>         


132
00:10:02,869 --> 00:10:05,036
        LET ME GET THAT.        


133
00:10:05,104 --> 00:10:08,139
        [ Breathing Heavily ]   
ARE YOU OKAY?                   


134
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:12,344
            I JUST LOST MY GRIP.
WHY DON'T YOU                   
COME SIT DOWN?                  


135
00:10:12,412 --> 00:10:15,613
            I'M A LITTLE DIZZY. 


136
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:18,215
UH, CAN I GET YOU SOMETHING?    
A GLASS OF WATER OR SOMETHING?  


137
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:20,417
        NO, I JUST NEED TO      
        CATCH MY BREATH.        


138
00:10:21,955 --> 00:10:25,456
    - CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?  
    - SURE.                     


139
00:10:25,525 --> 00:10:29,126
        - WHO ARE YOU?          
        - [ Chuckles ]          
          MY NAME IS JAROD.     


140
00:10:29,195 --> 00:10:30,795
                ANGELA.         


141
00:10:30,864 --> 00:10:33,931
    I, UH, NEED TO PUT          
    THESE THINGS IN THE SHED.   


142
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:36,267
<i>NO, NO. LET ME GET THAT.</i>        


143
00:10:36,336 --> 00:10:40,605
- ARE YOU LEARNING TO JUMP?     
- UH, NO. ACTUALLY, I JUST      
  STARTED WORKING HERE.         


144
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:56,754
YOU'RE THE NEW INSTRUCTOR.      
        YOU SOUND DISAPPOINTED. 


145
00:10:56,823 --> 00:11:01,258
I JUST DIDN'T EXPECT CAROL      
TO HIRE SOMEONE SO SOON AFTER-- 


146
00:11:03,396 --> 00:11:06,764
                    WHAT?       
BABY'S KICKING.                 


147
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:10,502
HE MUST NOT LIKE THE HEAT.      
                    IT'S A BOY? 


148
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:12,871
            HIS FATHER MUST BE  
            VERY PROUD.         


149
00:11:12,939 --> 00:11:15,039
            HIS FATHER'S DEAD.  


150
00:11:20,714 --> 00:11:24,448
THE FIRST RULE OF SKYDIVING     
IS TO RESPECT YOUR EQUIPMENT.   


151
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:27,785
    BECAUSE WITHOUT IT, YOU DIE.
    DO YOU UNDERSTAND?          


152
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:29,787
             [ All ]            
            <i> HAI.</i>               


153
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:33,424
    NOW, THE KEY TO A SAFE JUMP 
    IS TO OPEN YOUR CHUTE       
    AT THE RIGHT ALTITUDE.      


154
00:11:33,493 --> 00:11:36,260
    AND WE DO THAT BY PULLING   
    THE SILVER HANDLE.          


155
00:11:36,329 --> 00:11:39,129
            <i> WE DO</i> NOT<i> PULL</i>     
            <i> THE ORANGE HANDLE.</i> 


156
00:11:39,198 --> 00:11:41,533
    YOU READY TO GIVE IT A TRY? 


157
00:11:46,740 --> 00:11:50,975
        ALL RIGHT.              
        WE'RE OVER THE TARGET,  
        AND WE JUMP.            


158
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:53,344
        <i> [ Jarod ]</i>              
        <i> THE GROUND</i>             
        <i> IS RUSHING TOWARDS US.</i> 


159
00:11:53,413 --> 00:11:56,213
            YOU ARE READY       
            TO OPEN YOUR CHUTE. 


160
00:11:56,282 --> 00:11:58,983
            <i> YOU PULL</i>           
            <i> THE SILVER HANDLE!</i> 
        [ Grunts ]              


161
00:12:00,619 --> 00:12:02,887
        [ Engine Winds Down ]   


162
00:12:02,956 --> 00:12:05,523
    I GUESS IT LOST SOMETHIN'   
    IN THE TRANSLATION.         


163
00:12:05,592 --> 00:12:07,825
        <i> [ Grunting ]</i>           


164
00:12:09,596 --> 00:12:12,130
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>BENJAMIN THOMAS MILLER.</i>         
<i>SINGLE.</i>                         


165
00:12:12,199 --> 00:12:14,165
<i>RUNS THE LOCAL</i>                  
<i>BED-AND-BREAKFAST.</i>              


166
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:16,901
        I'M LOOKING FOR DIRT,   
        SYDNEY.                 


167
00:12:16,970 --> 00:12:21,539
THERE ISN'T ANY.                
I DON'T THINK HE'S EVEN         
HAD A PARKING TICKET.           


168
00:12:21,608 --> 00:12:24,209
<i>[ Sydney ] NOT HIM.</i>             
    <i> WELL, THEN WHY WOULD JAROD</i> 
    <i> LEAD US HERE?</i>              


169
00:12:24,277 --> 00:12:28,980
<i>HE DIDN'T. THE LITTLE</i>           
<i>RED NOTEBOOK WAS</i>                
<i>THE MISS PARKER EDITION.</i>        


170
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:30,882
        MEANING?                


171
00:12:30,950 --> 00:12:33,551
            HE WANTED YOU HERE, 
            ALONE.              


172
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,553
        <i> [ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i> 


173
00:12:38,257 --> 00:12:40,191
                WHAT?           


174
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:42,193
        [ Jarod ]               
        LET'S SEE. IT'S 12:00   
        NOON, WHERE YOU ARE.    


175
00:12:42,261 --> 00:12:44,195
            I RECOMMEND         
            THE MONTE CRISTO.   


176
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:47,899
    YOU CAN'T BEAT A SANDWICH   
    WITH SYRUP.                 


177
00:12:47,968 --> 00:12:51,236
IT IS A<i> LITTLE BIT</i> FATTENING.   


178
00:12:51,304 --> 00:12:54,505
WHAT THE HEY. YOU COULD STAND   
TO PUT ON A FEW POUNDS.         


179
00:12:54,574 --> 00:12:56,507
    HOW WOULD YOU KNOW?         


180
00:12:56,576 --> 00:12:58,709
OH, YOU NEVER KNOW WHO MIGHT BE 
PEEKING OVER YOUR TRANSOM.      


181
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:03,447
UH, UH, UH. SETTING BACK        
THE BATHROOM SCALE THREE        
POUNDS, THAT'S CHEATING.        


182
00:13:03,516 --> 00:13:06,751
WHAT DO YOU WANT, JAROD?        
            SAME THING YOU DO.  


183
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:08,853
                ANSWERS.        


184
00:13:08,922 --> 00:13:13,123
<i>BY NOW, I WOULD IMAGINE</i>         
<i>THAT YOU ARE STAKING OUT</i>        
<i>THE GREEN RIDGE DINER,</i>          


185
00:13:13,192 --> 00:13:15,793
            WHERE BEN MILLER IS 
            FINISHING UP        
            HIS USUAL LUNCH.    


186
00:13:15,862 --> 00:13:20,198
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>DIET COLA, B.L.T.,</i>              
<i>NO MAYO.</i>                        


187
00:13:20,267 --> 00:13:23,133
    I AM IMPRESSED WITH         
    YOUR EYE FOR DETAIL.        


188
00:13:23,203 --> 00:13:25,636
    I CAN SEE I'M GOING         
    TO HAVE TO SECURE           
    MY CELL PHONE NUMBER.       


189
00:13:25,705 --> 00:13:29,741
MMM. THOSE CENTRE OPERATORS,    
THEY WILL TRANSFER YOU ANYWHERE 
WITH THE RIGHT CLEARANCE CODE.  


190
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:31,742
                YOU SHOULD      
                LOOK INTO THAT. 


191
00:13:31,812 --> 00:13:35,046
    YEAH, I WOULD. EXCEPT       
    I'M TOO BUSY CHASING GHOSTS.


192
00:13:35,115 --> 00:13:38,616
    - WELL, BEN MILLER,         
      HE'S MORE OF A SKELETON.  
    -<i> [ Miss Parker ] SKELETON?</i> 


193
00:13:38,684 --> 00:13:41,819
    CHECK YOUR CLOSET LATELY?   


194
00:13:48,227 --> 00:13:50,628
            GET OUT.            


195
00:13:50,697 --> 00:13:53,097
<i>EXCUSE ME?</i>                      
                GET OUT.        


196
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:57,802
        TRY THE MONTE CRISTO.   
        I HEAR IT'S EXCELLENT.  


197
00:14:03,343 --> 00:14:05,276
                        READY?  
    <i> HAI!</i>                       


198
00:14:05,345 --> 00:14:08,546
                    <i> SAYONARA.</i>  
        [ Yelling ]             


199
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:12,784
                    READY?      
        <i> HAI!</i>                   


200
00:14:12,852 --> 00:14:14,985
                    <i> SAYONARA!</i>  
        [ Yells ]               


201
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:29,967
                HEY.            
                WHAT'S THIS FOR?


202
00:14:31,271 --> 00:14:33,471
FOR LUNATICS.                   


203
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:46,016
[ Wind Blowing ]                


204
00:14:55,862 --> 00:14:57,829
<i>[ Jarod Laughing ]</i>              
<i>THIS WAS AWESOME.</i>               


205
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:00,298
YOU KNOW, THIS THING WOULD      
WORK REALLY WELL IN THE SNOW.   


206
00:15:01,334 --> 00:15:03,267
        [ Clears Throat ]       
        YEAH.                   


207
00:15:04,804 --> 00:15:07,137
<i>CAROL BATES SAYS</i>                
<i>YOU USED TO BE A SKYDIVER.</i>      


208
00:15:09,475 --> 00:15:11,475
<i>YOU MISS IT?</i>                    
                IT?             


209
00:15:11,544 --> 00:15:16,213
THE ADRENALINE RUSH.            
PUSHING THE ENVELOPE AND        
LIVING TO TELL ABOUT IT.        


210
00:15:16,282 --> 00:15:19,717
WELL, SOMETIMES THAT ENVELOPE'S 
A LITTLE THINNER THAN IT LOOKS. 


211
00:15:19,786 --> 00:15:22,153
YOU TALKING ABOUT TOM MILES?    


212
00:15:23,189 --> 00:15:26,257
        I TOOK HIM UP THAT DAY. 


213
00:15:26,326 --> 00:15:30,160
YOU KNOW, THE SAD PART IS,      
THAT WAS GONNA BE HIS LAST JUMP.


214
00:15:30,229 --> 00:15:33,764
ISN'T IT A LITTLE DIFFICULT     
TO RUN A JUMP SCHOOL            
IF YOU DON'T JUMP?              


215
00:15:33,833 --> 00:15:38,336
    HEY. THIS<i> SCHOOL</i> HAS JUST   
    BARELY EKED BY FOR YEARS.   


216
00:15:38,404 --> 00:15:42,673
TOM DIDN'T CARE ABOUT           
ANY OF THAT. HE WAS JUST        
A PLAIN OLD SIMPLE GUY.         


217
00:15:42,742 --> 00:15:46,377
ALL HE REALLY CARED ABOUT WAS   
HIS WIFE AND THAT BABY COMIN'.  


218
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:49,613
            [ Sighs ]           
            HE LOVED THIS PLACE.


219
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:52,316
HE JUST WANTED TO HAVE A CHANCE 
TO SHARE IT WITH HIS SON...     


220
00:15:52,385 --> 00:15:54,352
    BEFORE SOMEBODY COME ALONG  
    AND SPOILED IT.             


221
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:58,956
<i>EXPECT HE PUSHED THAT ENVELOPE</i>  
<i>ONE TOO MANY TIMES.</i>             


222
00:15:59,024 --> 00:16:01,692
<i>FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND, TOM</i>     
<i>WAS A SURVIVAL EXPERT.</i>          


223
00:16:01,761 --> 00:16:06,764
HE SUCCESSFULLY MADE THAT JUMP  
AND TREK INTO THE DESERT        
A DOZEN TIMES BEFORE HE DIED.   


224
00:16:06,832 --> 00:16:10,134
    JUST 'CAUSE YOU             
    CAN DO SOMETHING,           
    DOESN'T MEAN YOU SHOULD.    


225
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:14,071
    BUT, HEY, IT'S THE DESERT.  
    STRANGE THINGS              
    CAN HAPPEN OUT THERE.       


226
00:16:26,252 --> 00:16:30,788
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>SO MANY LIES, SO LITTLE TIME.</i>   


227
00:16:32,558 --> 00:16:34,759
            YOU NEED SOME SODA. 


228
00:16:34,828 --> 00:16:39,130
- WHO ARE YOU?                  
- TWO FEATHERS, SON OF          
  WAR EAGLE. EVER HEARD OF ME?  


229
00:16:39,198 --> 00:16:40,898
        NO.                     


230
00:16:40,967 --> 00:16:43,801
        THAT'S 'CAUSE EVERYBODY 
        CALLS ME ERNIE.         


231
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:49,941
    I'M GUESSING IT'S A PEACH.  


232
00:16:56,182 --> 00:16:58,849
        -<i> [ Ernie ] HOW.</i>        
        -<i> [ Jarod Exhales ]</i>     


233
00:16:58,918 --> 00:17:00,317
            WHAT IS IT YOU WANT?


234
00:17:00,386 --> 00:17:04,021
I TOLD YOU I WAS SENT           
TO BE YOUR GUIDE.               
                        <i> YES.</i>   


235
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:06,958
    THE SKY FATHERS WHO         
    SPEAK TO YOU FROM YOUR GUT. 


236
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:08,659
        BINGO.                  


237
00:17:08,727 --> 00:17:10,794
                WHERE ARE YOU   
                GUIDING ME TO?  
<i>THE TRUTH.</i>                      


238
00:17:10,863 --> 00:17:14,298
I KNOW IT'S OVERWHELMING,       
BUT I'M AN INDIAN, SO WHAT      
DO YOU WANT FROM ME?            


239
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:15,966
<i>MEET ME TONIGHT.</i>                


240
00:17:16,035 --> 00:17:18,435
    WE CAN TALK LATER.          
                        <i> WAIT.</i>  


241
00:17:18,504 --> 00:17:22,206
    - HOW WILL I FIND YOU?      
    - FOLLOW THE PATH           
      OF THE IRON HORSE.        


242
00:17:22,275 --> 00:17:27,779
- THE WHAT?                     
- THE TRAIN TRACKS. DIDN'T YOU  
  EVER SEE A JOHN WAYNE MOVIE?  


243
00:17:27,847 --> 00:17:30,348
AND BRING SOME OF THAT          
LEFTOVER MEAT LOAF WITH YOU.    


244
00:17:30,416 --> 00:17:32,316
        - WHAT MEAT LOAF?       
        - [ Wind Blows ]        


245
00:17:32,384 --> 00:17:34,651
            [ Lamp Shatters ]   


246
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:38,655
                [ Exhales ]     


247
00:17:43,128 --> 00:17:45,062
                HUH.            
        <i> [ Knocking On Door ]</i>   


248
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:47,665
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU</i>            
<i>THINK YOU'RE DEALING WITH,</i>      


249
00:17:47,734 --> 00:17:49,533
BUT I'M GETTING PRETTY TIRED    
OF YOUR MAGIC TR--              


250
00:17:49,602 --> 00:17:51,535
    I HAVE TO ADMIT.            
    I'VE HAD WARMER WELCOMES.   


251
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:56,140
        DID YOU SEE AN OLD MAN? 


252
00:17:58,077 --> 00:17:59,944
                HUH.            


253
00:18:01,013 --> 00:18:02,980
            NEVER MIND.         


254
00:18:03,049 --> 00:18:07,217
I, UM, WANTED TO APOLOGIZE      
FOR THE WAY I ACTED YESTERDAY.  


255
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:10,554
- OH, IT'S OKAY.                
- NO, YOU'RE NEW HERE. THERE'S  
  NO WAY YOU COULD'VE KNOWN.    


256
00:18:10,623 --> 00:18:12,556
AND... I'D LIKE TO              
MAKE IT UP TO YOU.              


257
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:15,759
<i>HOW ABOUT</i>                       
<i>A HOME-COOKED DINNER TONIGHT?</i>   
        THAT WOULD BE WONDERFUL.


258
00:18:15,828 --> 00:18:17,662
GREAT.                          
HOPE YOU LIKE MEAT LOAF.        


259
00:18:31,711 --> 00:18:34,411
[ Door Creaking ]               


260
00:18:36,682 --> 00:18:38,615
    BE RIGHT WITH YOU.          


261
00:18:41,654 --> 00:18:44,188
        NOW, WHAT CAN I DO FOR--


262
00:18:47,025 --> 00:18:49,192
I WAS HOPING YOU'D COME.        


263
00:18:49,261 --> 00:18:51,796
    WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT? 


264
00:18:53,032 --> 00:18:54,965
YOU LOOK JUST LIKE HER.         


265
00:18:55,034 --> 00:18:57,768
                LIKE WHO?       


266
00:18:57,837 --> 00:18:59,469
    YOUR MOTHER.                


267
00:19:18,357 --> 00:19:20,891
    THANK YOU.                  


268
00:19:28,001 --> 00:19:30,701
    I'M SURE THIS               
    WON'T TAKE LONG.            


269
00:19:34,574 --> 00:19:37,641
    SHERIFF, I WAS WONDERING    
    IF I MIGHT HAVE A MINUTE.   


270
00:19:37,710 --> 00:19:41,812
    MR. COCHRAN, I'M DUE IN     
    DALLAS IN ABOUT THREE HOURS.
    MAYBE SOME OTHER TIME.      


271
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:44,515
OH, OKAY. I JUST WANTED TO ASK  
YOU A QUESTION ABOUT TOM MILES. 


272
00:19:44,584 --> 00:19:46,951
BUT WE'LL DO IT                 
ANOTHER TIME.                   
            WHAT ABOUT TOM?     


273
00:19:49,088 --> 00:19:51,188
WELL, I UNDERSTAND THAT         
YOU FOUND HIS BODY.             


274
00:19:51,257 --> 00:19:53,591
                THAT'S RIGHT.   
<i>MUST HAVE BEEN</i>                  
<i>A PRETTY GRUESOME SIGHT.</i>        


275
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:57,627
BODY OUT THERE IN THE DESERT    
FOR, WHAT, THREE DAYS?          


276
00:19:57,696 --> 00:20:00,031
                    FOUR.       
<i>FOUR, UGH.</i>                      


277
00:20:01,233 --> 00:20:03,701
SEE, WHAT                       
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IS...        


278
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:07,871
WHY WOULD A SURVIVAL EXPERT     
LIKE TOM MILES ALLOW HIMSELF    
TO DIE OF DEHYDRATION?          


279
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:11,442
    WHAT ARE YOU SO INTERESTED  
    IN A DEAD MAN FOR?          


280
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:14,845
WELL, I MET HIS WIDOW.          
SEEMED LIKE A VERY NICE LADY.   


281
00:20:14,914 --> 00:20:17,014
    NEVER MIND.                 
    HAVE A VERY NICE DAY.       


282
00:20:18,951 --> 00:20:22,486
OH, SHERIFF,                    
ONE OTHER QUICK QUESTION.       


283
00:20:22,555 --> 00:20:24,521
    WAS THERE AN AUTOPSY        
    DONE ON THE BODY?           


284
00:20:26,593 --> 00:20:30,995
OF COURSE. JUST BECAUSE         
WE LIVE IN THE BACKWATERS       
DOESN'T MEAN WE'RE BACKWOODS.   


285
00:20:31,064 --> 00:20:32,296
    THANK YOU VERY MUCH.        


286
00:20:48,481 --> 00:20:50,414
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>SHE ATE THE WHOLE MEAT LOAF?</i>    


287
00:20:50,483 --> 00:20:53,384
    WELL, THEN IT IS NO WONDER  
    SHE CAN'T FIND PANTY HOSE...


288
00:20:53,453 --> 00:20:56,053
    TO FIT THOSE THICK THIGHS   
    OF HERS THEN, HUH?          


289
00:20:56,122 --> 00:20:58,789
[ Door Opens ]                  
                    YEAH.       
                    [ Chuckles ]


290
00:20:58,858 --> 00:21:01,192
        OH. I'LL CALL YOU LATER.


291
00:21:05,598 --> 00:21:07,698
                    <i> [ Jarod ]</i>  
                    <i> AFTERNOON.</i> 
    AFTERNOON.                  


292
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:10,400
        BUDDY SLOCUM JR.        


293
00:21:10,469 --> 00:21:13,838
I REPRESENT THE SOUTHWEST       
REGIONAL OFFICE OF              
THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.   


294
00:21:13,906 --> 00:21:15,840
    I.R.S.?                     


295
00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:21,244
    I NEED TO HAVE A WORD WITH  
    A SHERIFF DWIGHT KNUCKLE.   


296
00:21:21,313 --> 00:21:25,015
KUNKLE. THE SHERIFF'S NAME      
IS KUNKLE.                      


297
00:21:25,084 --> 00:21:30,020
SHERIFF KNUCK--<i> KUNKLE</i>          
IS IN DALLAS FOR THE AFTERNOON. 


298
00:21:30,089 --> 00:21:33,057
                WELL, THAT COULD
                POSE A DILEMMA. 


299
00:21:34,627 --> 00:21:37,527
<i>BUDDY. MAYBE I CAN HELP YOU.</i>    


300
00:21:37,596 --> 00:21:41,832
    <i> YES. AS A MATTER OF FACT,</i>  
    <i> MAYBE YOU CAN.</i>             


301
00:21:43,235 --> 00:21:46,403
    DO YOU HAVE SOME INFORMATION
    ON A MR. THOMAS MILES?      


302
00:21:46,472 --> 00:21:48,205
    WELL, HE'S DEAD.            


303
00:21:48,274 --> 00:21:50,808
        NOT AS FAR AS THE I.R.S.
        IS CONCERNED.           


304
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:56,246
    WELL, THANKS AGAIN, MA'AM.  


305
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,567
<i>[ Angela ]</i>                      
<i>TOM WAS GONNA FINISH THE BABY'S</i> 
<i>ROOM WHEN HE GOT BACK.</i>          


306
00:22:17,636 --> 00:22:20,404
HE MUST HAVE BEEN VERY EXCITED  
ABOUT BECOMING A FATHER.        


307
00:22:20,473 --> 00:22:22,906
<i>[ Angela ]</i>                      
<i>IT WAS HIS WHOLE WORLD.</i>         


308
00:22:24,877 --> 00:22:27,277
BEFORE TOM WENT OFF             
ON THE LAST JUMP,               


309
00:22:27,346 --> 00:22:30,147
HE TOLD ME HOW IMPORTANT IT WAS 
FOR HIM TO BE A<i> GOOD</i> FATHER,    


310
00:22:30,216 --> 00:22:33,150
<i>TO TEACH OUR SON ABOUT LIFE.</i>    


311
00:22:33,219 --> 00:22:36,453
<i>HE USED TO SAY THAT</i>             
<i>LIFE WAS MEANT TO BE LIVED,</i>     


312
00:22:36,522 --> 00:22:38,989
AND DEATH WASN'T                
SOMETHING TO BE AFRAID OF.      


313
00:22:39,058 --> 00:22:41,625
IS THAT WHY HE MADE             
THOSE JUMPS INTO THE DESERT?    


314
00:22:45,531 --> 00:22:49,933
<i>CAROL'S RIGHT.</i>                  
<i>IT'S IMPORTANT THAT HIS SON</i>     
<i>KNOW WHO HIS FATHER WAS.</i>        


315
00:22:50,002 --> 00:22:52,269
- THE THINGS HE CARED ABOUT.    
- CAROL SAID THAT.              


316
00:22:52,337 --> 00:22:56,173
<i>SHE SAID THAT IF THE SCHOOL</i>     
<i>CLOSED, THEN TOM'S DEATH</i>        
<i>WOULD BE MEANINGLESS.</i>           


317
00:22:56,242 --> 00:22:59,309
    - THANK GOD                 
      FOR TOM'S INSURANCE MONEY.
    - WHAT DO YOU MEAN?         


318
00:22:59,378 --> 00:23:04,214
    WE'RE GONNA USE IT          
    TO REBUILD THE JUMP SCHOOL. 
    HASN'T BEEN EASY FOR HER.   


319
00:23:04,283 --> 00:23:06,716
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>BECAUSE OF THE BUSINESS?</i>        


320
00:23:06,785 --> 00:23:10,287
    BECAUSE OF THE HISTORY      
    BETWEEN THEM.               


321
00:23:10,355 --> 00:23:14,791
- THE HISTORY?                  
- CAROL AND TOM WERE TOGETHER   
  LONG BEFORE WE MET.           


322
00:23:14,860 --> 00:23:17,661
    THEY GREW APART, FELL OUT.  


323
00:23:17,730 --> 00:23:22,366
    <i> HE USED TO SAY</i>             
    <i> SHE WAS UNHAPPY, BUT HE</i>    
    <i> NEVER SPOKE BAD ABOUT HER.</i> 


324
00:23:22,435 --> 00:23:25,803
I THINK IT'S NICE               
THAT SHE WANTS TO KEEP          
HIS DREAM ALIVE.                


325
00:23:34,713 --> 00:23:36,647
[ Beeping ]                     


326
00:23:38,350 --> 00:23:42,753
JUST TELL ME YOU'VE GIVEN UP.   
                 [ Young Jarod ]
                 NO.            


327
00:23:42,822 --> 00:23:44,755
ADMIT IT TO YOURSELF            
AND I'LL MAKE THIS STOP!        


328
00:23:45,825 --> 00:23:48,325
            NOT FOR ME.         


329
00:23:48,393 --> 00:23:50,327
[ Young Jarod ]                 
I'LL NEVER GIVE UP.             


330
00:23:51,563 --> 00:23:54,164
[ Echoing ]                     
NEVER GIVE UP.                  


331
00:24:44,183 --> 00:24:46,350
            MR. TWO FEATHERS?   


332
00:24:48,987 --> 00:24:51,087
        UH, MR. TWO FEATHERS?   


333
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:54,024
                    ERNIE?      


334
00:24:54,093 --> 00:24:57,360
OH!                             
[ Gasps ]                       


335
00:24:57,429 --> 00:24:59,964
WOULD YOU PLEASE                
STOP DOING THAT?                


336
00:25:00,032 --> 00:25:02,432
        I SEE YOU REMEMBERED.   
        THANK YOU.              


337
00:25:03,435 --> 00:25:06,269
YOUR MEAT LOAF.                 
YOU LEFT YOUR HAT.              


338
00:25:06,338 --> 00:25:09,039
                    THANK YOU.  
                    SIT DOWN.   


339
00:25:11,477 --> 00:25:13,444
IS THIS WHERE YOU LIVE?         


340
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:16,747
YOU EXPECTED A TEEPEE?          


341
00:25:16,816 --> 00:25:19,816
IT'S 43 FEET OF GOOD LIVING,    
SATELLITE TV.                   


342
00:25:19,885 --> 00:25:22,753
        I EVEN GET DIRTY MOVIES.


343
00:25:22,821 --> 00:25:25,889
    - COMPLIMENTS OF UNCLE SAM. 
    - UNCLE WHO?                


344
00:25:25,958 --> 00:25:30,260
THERE WAS A QUESTION ABOUT      
A CERTAIN PIECE OF TRIBAL LAND  
AND WHO OWNED IT.               


345
00:25:30,329 --> 00:25:33,630
AND THIS WAS YOUR SETTLEMENT?   
I WOULD'VE SETTLED              
FOR A NEW HAT.                  


346
00:25:33,699 --> 00:25:36,766
<i>WHITE PEOPLE.</i>                   
<i>I DON'T KNOW HOW</i>                
<i>WE LOST THE COUNTRY.</i>            


347
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:41,872
YOU TOLD ME BEFORE THAT YOU WERE
GOING TO GUIDE ME TO THE TRUTH. 


348
00:25:41,941 --> 00:25:43,973
<i>OH, THAT.</i>                       


349
00:25:45,710 --> 00:25:50,414
MY FAMILY'S LIVED UNDER THIS    
SKY FOR OVER SEVEN GENERATIONS. 


350
00:25:50,482 --> 00:25:53,483
<i>I'VE SEEN MANY THINGS</i>           
<i>IN THE DESERT.</i>                  


351
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,152
                THINGS?         


352
00:25:55,221 --> 00:25:59,089
    I FOUND THE BODY OF THE MAN 
    WHO WALKS ON CLOUDS.        


353
00:25:59,157 --> 00:26:02,259
        I THOUGHT SHERIFF KUNKLE
        FOUND TOM MILES'S BODY. 


354
00:26:02,328 --> 00:26:04,795
IT WOULDN'T BE SMART FOR        
AN INDIAN TO RIDE INTO TOWN...  


355
00:26:04,863 --> 00:26:08,098
WITH A WHITE WAR HERO           
STRAPPED ACROSS                 
THE GRILLE OF HIS MOTOR HOME.   


356
00:26:08,167 --> 00:26:13,503
WHY WOULD A SURVIVAL EXPERT LIKE
TOM MILES DIE OF DEHYDRATION... 


357
00:26:13,572 --> 00:26:15,706
    WHEN ALL THOSE YUCCA PLANTS 
    WERE AROUND HIM?            


358
00:26:15,774 --> 00:26:18,341
    WHEN I SAW HIS FACE,        
    I KNEW WHAT HAPPENED.       


359
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,210
        <i> ACCORDING</i>              
        <i> TO THE POLICE REPORT,</i>  


360
00:26:20,279 --> 00:26:23,213
    THE WOUNDS ON HIS FACE      
    WERE INFLICTED BY AN ANIMAL.


361
00:26:23,282 --> 00:26:27,517
        IT WAS NO ANIMAL.       
         IT WAS HIS MADNESS.    


362
00:26:27,586 --> 00:26:29,686
<i>I'VE SEEN IT ONLY</i>               
<i>ONE TIME BEFORE IN MY LIFE--</i>    


363
00:26:29,755 --> 00:26:31,989
        DURING THE VISION QUEST.


364
00:26:32,058 --> 00:26:33,657
            VISION QUEST?       


365
00:26:33,726 --> 00:26:38,829
    A YOUNG MAN OF AGE          
    DRINKS FROM THE ROOT        
    OF THE BELLADONNA PLANT...  


366
00:26:38,897 --> 00:26:43,566
    IN THE HOPES OF             
    GOING TO THE WORLD BEYOND.  


367
00:26:43,635 --> 00:26:47,503
IF THE MIXTURE IS WRONG,        
HE COULD LOSE HIMSELF, GO MAD.  


368
00:26:50,242 --> 00:26:52,175
        BELLADONNA.             


369
00:26:55,748 --> 00:26:57,680
WHO ELSE KNOWS ABOUT THIS PLANT?


370
00:26:57,749 --> 00:27:00,918
ANYONE WHO'S LIVED THEIR LIFE   
IN THE DESERT WOULD KNOW.       


371
00:27:03,221 --> 00:27:06,523
        I SEE YOUR GUT          
        TALKS TO YOU TOO.       


372
00:27:12,931 --> 00:27:15,165
    HMM. THIS IS PRETTY GOOD.   


373
00:27:16,468 --> 00:27:19,235
        <i> JAROD WORKED THE PLACE</i> 
        <i> ABOUT A MONTH.</i>         


374
00:27:19,304 --> 00:27:22,005
        HE WAS QUITE            
        THE FIX-IT MAN.         


375
00:27:22,074 --> 00:27:25,508
                HE'S A GENIUS.  
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.        


376
00:27:25,577 --> 00:27:28,545
BUT HE COULD FIX A TRACTOR,     
TALK YOUR EAR OFF.              


377
00:27:28,614 --> 00:27:31,515
THAT FELLA WAS ALWAYS           
ASKIN' QUESTIONS.               


378
00:27:33,285 --> 00:27:36,019
            I DIDN'T COME HERE  
            TO TALK ABOUT JAROD.


379
00:27:36,087 --> 00:27:40,724
WELL, THAT'S FUNNY. ALL HE      
WANTED TO TALK ABOUT WAS YOU.   


380
00:27:40,793 --> 00:27:45,095
                        ME?     
HE SAID YOU TWO HAD             
GROWN UP TOGETHER.              


381
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:48,465
SEEMED DISAPPOINTED             
WHEN I DIDN'T KNOW MUCH.        


382
00:27:48,533 --> 00:27:52,502
GUESS YOUR MOTHER NEVER         
TOLD YOU ABOUT THIS PLACE.      


383
00:27:52,571 --> 00:27:55,405
                    NO.         
                    SHE DIDN'T. 


384
00:27:55,474 --> 00:27:59,075
SHE CAME HERE EXACTLY           
THIS TIME EVERY YEAR.           


385
00:27:59,144 --> 00:28:01,911
SHE LOVED THE SPRING.           


386
00:28:01,980 --> 00:28:05,082
<i>SHE SAID SHE LIKED</i>              
<i>WHAT IT DID TO THE WORLD.</i>       


387
00:28:08,787 --> 00:28:10,721
    AUNT DOROTHY.               


388
00:28:10,789 --> 00:28:12,889
    EXCUSE ME?                  


389
00:28:12,958 --> 00:28:16,460
SHE USED TO TELL ME             
 SHE WAS VISITING HER SISTER.   


390
00:28:16,528 --> 00:28:20,497
<i>AH.</i>                             
<i>I'M SURE SHE HAD HER REASONS.</i>   


391
00:28:22,535 --> 00:28:26,002
WHEN YOUR MOTHER DIDN'T         
SHOW UP, I GOT WORRIED.         


392
00:28:28,073 --> 00:28:30,239
I NEVER KNEW EXACTLY HOW--      


393
00:28:30,308 --> 00:28:34,411
            I WAS PRETTY YOUNG. 


394
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:39,316
    BUT I DO REMEMBER THAT      
    HER DEATH WAS, UH, SUDDEN.  


395
00:28:42,955 --> 00:28:46,222
    IS THERE ANYTHING OF HERS-- 


396
00:28:46,291 --> 00:28:49,593
IT WOULD MEAN A LOT TO ME       
IF I COULD SEE WHERE SHE STAYED.


397
00:28:54,767 --> 00:28:57,034
<i>[ Crockett ]</i>                    
<i>LOOK HERE, CAROL,</i>               
<i>IT'S JUST NOT WORKIN' OUT!</i>      


398
00:28:57,102 --> 00:28:59,035
<i>I HAVE TO MOVE ON.</i>              


399
00:28:59,104 --> 00:29:02,872
    ONCE WE GET THE NEW PLANE   
    FROM PHOENIX, WE'RE FINE.   
YOU KNOW I CAN'T GO BACK THERE! 


400
00:29:16,321 --> 00:29:18,255
[ Rifling Papers ]              


401
00:29:34,105 --> 00:29:36,039
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>TASCO SPORT ADVENTURE.</i>          


402
00:29:36,108 --> 00:29:38,842
<i>[ Jarod ] I'M TRYING TO</i>         
<i>PUT TOGETHER A VACATION.</i>        
<i>YOU COME HIGHLY RECOMMENDED.</i>    


403
00:29:38,911 --> 00:29:41,945
    YES, SIR. AT TASCO          
    SPORT ADVENTURE, YOU GET    
    THE VACATION OF A LIFETIME. 


404
00:29:42,014 --> 00:29:44,013
BUNGEE JUMPING AND THEN GOLF,   


405
00:29:44,083 --> 00:29:47,384
<i>HELICOPTER SNOW SKIING IN</i>       
<i>THE ANDES, OR SHARK HUNTING</i>     
<i>OFF THE BARRIER REEF.</i>           


406
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:49,753
        ACTUALLY,               
        I HAD SKYDIVING IN MIND.


407
00:29:49,822 --> 00:29:53,323
YOU'RE IN LUCK! IN TWO MONTHS,  
WE'RE OPENING A SKYDIVING SCHOOL
NEAR EL PASO.                   


408
00:29:53,391 --> 00:29:58,027
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>WELL, THAT SOUNDS INTERESTING.</i>  
<i>VERY INTERESTING.</i>               


409
00:29:58,096 --> 00:30:02,099
    - UH, I'LL LET YOU KNOW.    
    -<i> THANKS FOR CALLING.</i>       


410
00:30:26,758 --> 00:30:29,359
[ Tools Clanking ]              


411
00:30:35,867 --> 00:30:39,535
            [ Wrench Racheting ]
            OW!                 


412
00:30:39,604 --> 00:30:41,905
[ Slams Tools Down ]            
    PIECE OF CRAP!              


413
00:30:41,974 --> 00:30:44,074
        OH, COME ON, CROCKETT.  
GOD! OH--                       


414
00:30:44,142 --> 00:30:47,443
[ Inhales, Coughs ]             
        PLANE ONLY HAS TO       
        LAST A FEW MORE DAYS.   


415
00:30:47,512 --> 00:30:50,080
YOU SCARED ME THERE, BUB.       
                        WHY?    


416
00:30:50,149 --> 00:30:54,651
    BECAUSE YOU THOUGHT I WAS   
    CAROL? SHE SCARES YOU,      
    DOESN'T SHE, CROCKETT?      


417
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:58,387
        OR SHOULD I SAY ANGUS?  
        ANGUS MARIN?            


418
00:30:59,858 --> 00:31:01,792
    WHO ARE YOU?                


419
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:04,427
        SOMEBODY WHO FOUND OUT  
        YOU'RE A WANTED MAN...  


420
00:31:04,496 --> 00:31:06,429
        AND IS GOING TO USE IT  
        TO THEIR ADVANTAGE.     


421
00:31:06,498 --> 00:31:10,967
        <i> JUST LIKE CAROL DID.</i>   
YOU SOUND LIKE YOU<i> HAVE</i> BEEN    
DRINKING THAT HORSE LINIMENT.   


422
00:31:11,036 --> 00:31:13,970
    <i> I KNOW CAROL'S USING ANGELA</i>
    <i> TO GET TO TOM MILES'S</i>      
    <i> INSURANCE MONEY.</i>           


423
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:16,305
            SO SHE CAN REFURBISH
            THIS JUMP SCHOOL... 


424
00:31:16,374 --> 00:31:19,609
    AND INCREASE THE PRICE      
    THAT TASCO ADVENTURES       
    IS WILLING TO PAY FOR IT.   


425
00:31:19,678 --> 00:31:25,147
<i>I ALSO KNOW YOU ARE GETTING 25%</i> 
<i>OF WHATEVER CAROL'S STAKE IS</i>    
<i>IN THE SALE.</i>                    


426
00:31:25,216 --> 00:31:27,283
    WHAT I DON'T KNOW IS WHY.   


427
00:31:28,553 --> 00:31:30,620
        IS IT BECAUSE YOU KNOW  
        SHE KILLED TOM MILES?   


428
00:31:30,689 --> 00:31:32,722
    <i> OR BECAUSE YOU HELPED HER?</i> 


429
00:31:39,263 --> 00:31:41,197
THIS WAS HER ROOM.              


430
00:31:41,266 --> 00:31:44,000
<i>[ Ben ]</i>                         
<i>I HAVEN'T TOUCHED ANYTHING</i>      
<i>SINCE SHE LEFT.</i>                 


431
00:31:51,175 --> 00:31:53,710
        -<i> [ Soft Chuckle ]</i>      
        - WHAT?                 


432
00:31:53,778 --> 00:31:57,847
LOOKING AT YOU STANDING THERE,  
I THOUGHT FOR A MINUTE          
I SAW CATHERINE AGAIN.          


433
00:32:00,185 --> 00:32:02,818
YOU CALL IF YOU NEED ANYTHING.  


434
00:33:14,826 --> 00:33:19,762
    SEE, TOM AND CAROL COME     
    OUT HERE AS YOUNG LOVERS,   
    BOUGHT THIS PLACE TOGETHER. 


435
00:33:19,831 --> 00:33:22,498
        ONLY IT WAS 60-40,      
        TOM'S FAVOR.            


436
00:33:22,567 --> 00:33:25,167
            AFTER THEY BROKE UP,
            HE MET ANGELA       
            AND GOT MARRIED.    


437
00:33:25,236 --> 00:33:27,503
        HE WAS HERE FOR LIFE,   
        AND CAROL KNEW IT.      


438
00:33:27,572 --> 00:33:30,206
        SHE WANTED TO SELL,     
        BUT HE COULD NEVER      
        GET THE CASH TOGETHER.  


439
00:33:30,274 --> 00:33:33,376
BY THAT TIME, THE PLACE         
HAD GOTTEN SO RUN DOWN TILL--   


440
00:33:33,444 --> 00:33:35,578
        40% OF NOTHING'S        
        STILL NOTHIN'.          


441
00:33:35,647 --> 00:33:38,214
AND THAT'S WHEN THE PEOPLE      
FROM TASCO CAME AROUND.         


442
00:33:38,283 --> 00:33:41,117
            WAVIN' LONG GREEN.  


443
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:43,153
    BUT TOM DIDN'T              
    WANT THE PLACE DESTROYED.   


444
00:33:43,221 --> 00:33:47,958
    <i> SO, WHEN CAROL COULDN'T</i>    
    <i> GET HER MONEY AND GET OUT,</i> 
    <i> SHE JUST SHUT DOWN.</i>        


445
00:33:48,026 --> 00:33:51,227
    THEN WHAT HAPPENED?         


446
00:33:51,296 --> 00:33:55,564
    SHE CAME OUT TO THE HANGAR  
    THE MORNING OF THE JUMP,    
    SWITCHED TOM'S CANTEEN.     


447
00:33:55,633 --> 00:34:00,103
I DIDN'T THINK ANYTHING         
ABOUT IT AT THE TIME.           
IT DIDN'T MEAN ANYTHING THEN.   


448
00:34:00,172 --> 00:34:06,075
BUT LATER ON, AFTER HE DIED,    
I GOT TO THINKIN' ABOUT IT.     
WHEN I ASKED HER--              


449
00:34:06,144 --> 00:34:08,645
SHE THREATENED TO TURN YOU IN   
TO THE POLICE.                  


450
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:10,646
    SHE OFFERED ME A PERCENTAGE,


451
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:13,749
        JUST TO HELP HER GET    
        THE PLACE TURNED AROUND 
        FOR THE SALE TO TASCO.  


452
00:34:13,818 --> 00:34:15,818
        <i> WE LOOKED AT EACH OTHER</i>
        <i> AND JUST KNEW.</i>         


453
00:34:15,887 --> 00:34:21,657
WILLING TO HATE EACH OTHER      
LONG ENOUGH TO GET OUR PAYOFFS  
AND GET ON WITH OUR LIVES.      


454
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:26,362
    WELL, UNFORTUNATELY         
    FOR TOM MILES, HE WON'T     
    BE ABLE TO GET ON WITH HIS. 


455
00:34:44,449 --> 00:34:47,050
    [ Wrench Clinking ]         


456
00:34:49,720 --> 00:34:52,888
[ Southern Accent ]             
YES. I'D LIKE TO ORDER          
A SLAB OF BEEF RIBS.            


457
00:34:52,958 --> 00:34:56,559
WELL, THAT'S FANTASTIC.         
BUT I'D LIKE THEM RAW.          


458
00:34:56,627 --> 00:34:58,661
        YES, RAW.               


459
00:35:19,717 --> 00:35:23,352
SO, LET'S GET THIS STRAIGHT.    
IF I ARRIVE IN PHOENIX FIRST,   
I GET THE PLANE?                


460
00:35:23,421 --> 00:35:25,955
WELL, I'LL GET THERE FIRST.     


461
00:35:42,507 --> 00:35:46,275
        HAVE YOU SEEN CROCKETT? 
        NO.                     


462
00:35:48,179 --> 00:35:50,112
IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG?       


463
00:35:50,181 --> 00:35:52,982
I JUST GOT A CALL FROM PHOENIX. 
THERE'S ANOTHER PARTY           
INTERESTED IN THE PLANE.        


464
00:35:53,051 --> 00:35:55,485
THEY'RE GONNA MAKE A DEAL       
WITH THE FIRST ONE WHO SHOWS UP!


465
00:35:55,554 --> 00:35:58,788
OH. WELL, SHOULDN'T BE MORE     
THAN A SIX OR SEVEN-HOUR DRIVE. 


466
00:35:58,857 --> 00:36:01,491
I DON'T HAVE SIX                
OR SEVEN HOURS.                 


467
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:03,793
        WELL, I COULD FLY YOU.  


468
00:36:04,963 --> 00:36:07,897
YOU'RE A PILOT?                 
                    MM-HMM.     


469
00:36:07,966 --> 00:36:11,734
HOW LONG TILL                   
WE CAN TAKE OFF?                
                TWENTY MINUTES. 


470
00:36:11,803 --> 00:36:14,804
<i>[ Ben ]</i>                         
<i>HOW 'BOUT SOME COFFEE?</i>          
<i>[ Miss Parker ] THANK YOU.</i>      


471
00:36:16,708 --> 00:36:19,609
    HOW'D YOU SLEEP?            
                        WELL.   


472
00:36:19,678 --> 00:36:21,711
            BETTER THAN THAT,   
            ACTUALLY.           


473
00:36:21,780 --> 00:36:24,614
    THIS PLACE TENDS            
    TO DO THAT TO PEOPLE.       


474
00:36:24,683 --> 00:36:27,450
SURE YOU DON'T WANT TO TAKE     
SOME OF HER THINGS WITH YA?     


475
00:36:28,453 --> 00:36:32,221
            NO. I HAVE          
            EVERYTHING I NEED.  


476
00:36:32,290 --> 00:36:34,690
            <i> BESIDES, THIS IS</i>   
            <i> WHERE SHE BELONGS.</i> 


477
00:36:36,962 --> 00:36:38,927
    YOU WERE IN LOVE WITH HER,  
    WEREN'T YOU?                


478
00:36:38,996 --> 00:36:42,565
YOUR MOTHER WAS                 
A VERY SPECIAL WOMAN.           


479
00:36:44,068 --> 00:36:48,204
<i>THERE WAS A PART OF HER</i>         
<i>I KNEW BETTER THAN ANYONE.</i>      


480
00:36:48,273 --> 00:36:50,840
BUT THERE WAS A PART OF HER     
SHE KEPT HIDDEN.                


481
00:36:50,909 --> 00:36:53,743
<i>SEPARATE.</i>                       
                DID SHE EVER    
                TALK ABOUT HIM? 


482
00:36:53,811 --> 00:36:56,879
NO. SHE LEFT IT ALL BEHIND      
WHEN SHE CAME HERE.             


483
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:03,219
BUT... SHE ALWAYS MISSED        
HER LITTLE GIRL.                


484
00:37:06,591 --> 00:37:08,591
    I'LL GET YOU SOME BREAKFAST.


485
00:37:10,495 --> 00:37:13,029
    THANK YOU.                  


486
00:37:20,672 --> 00:37:24,507
                WHY ARE WE      
                HEADING NORTH?  
WEATHER RADAR.                  


487
00:37:24,576 --> 00:37:27,142
THERE'S A STORM FRONT           
MOVING IN FROM THE SOUTHWEST,   


488
00:37:27,211 --> 00:37:29,912
SO I FIGURED IT WOULD BE SAFER  
IF WE FLEW AROUND IT.           


489
00:37:29,981 --> 00:37:31,914
            HOW LONG TO PHOENIX?


490
00:37:31,983 --> 00:37:35,985
ABOUT AN HOUR,                  
HOUR AND A HALF.                
            [ Engine Sputters ] 


491
00:37:37,622 --> 00:37:39,555
                WHAT'S WRONG?   


492
00:37:41,559 --> 00:37:43,826
WE'RE LOSING PRESSURE.          


493
00:37:46,832 --> 00:37:48,765
I THINK IT'S THE FUEL PUMP.     


494
00:37:53,504 --> 00:37:56,438
<i>THIS TERRAIN IS MUCH TOO</i>        
<i>DANGEROUS TO LAND.</i>              


495
00:37:56,507 --> 00:38:00,209
IF THE OVERFLOW OF FUEL         
SHOULD REACH THE ENGINE,        
THE WHOLE PLANE COULD EXPLODE.  


496
00:38:01,212 --> 00:38:03,146
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE TO JUMP.    


497
00:38:03,214 --> 00:38:05,014
                    JUMP?       
JUMP.                           


498
00:38:06,184 --> 00:38:11,087
RELAX. WE'RE SKYDIVING          
INSTRUCTORS, REMEMBER?          


499
00:38:11,155 --> 00:38:13,756
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU MEAN       
HE WAS POLITE?                  


500
00:38:13,824 --> 00:38:16,159
YOU JUST GIVE OUT CONFIDENTIAL  
CRIME SCENE FILES...            


501
00:38:16,227 --> 00:38:18,894
TO ANYBODY WHO                  
WALKS IN HERE WITH              
A SMILE ON THEIR FACE?          


502
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:21,030
            HE SAID HE WAS      
            WITH THE I.R.S.     


503
00:38:21,098 --> 00:38:23,032
DAMN IT, AIDA. I'VE             
TOLD YOU A MILLION TIMES.       


504
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:25,334
POLICE BUSINESS IS--            
<i>[ Jarod On Radio ]</i>              
<i>ALPHA-TANGO-997.</i>                


505
00:38:25,403 --> 00:38:28,103
<i>THIS IS A MAYDAY.</i>               
<i>I REPEAT, THIS IS A MAYDAY.</i>     


506
00:38:28,173 --> 00:38:30,105
<i>OUR AIRCRAFT IS ON FIRE.</i>        


507
00:38:30,175 --> 00:38:34,143
<i>WE'RE GOING TO PARACHUTE</i>        
<i>APPROXIMATELY 37 MILES</i>          
<i>DUE NORTH OF FORT HANCOCK.</i>      


508
00:38:34,212 --> 00:38:36,546
MAYDAY. MAYDAY.                 
[ Transmission Turns Off ]      


509
00:38:37,882 --> 00:38:40,917
    997-- THAT'S CAROL'S PLANE. 


510
00:38:40,986 --> 00:38:44,487
YOU CALL THE CIVIL AIR PATROL.  
DISPATCH SEARCH AND RESCUE      
RIGHT NOW.                      


511
00:38:48,226 --> 00:38:51,060
GOING MY WAY, SHERIFF?          


512
00:39:23,962 --> 00:39:26,195
        [ Grunting ]            


513
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:37,940
                ARE YOU OKAY?   
                [ Grunting ]    


514
00:39:38,009 --> 00:39:42,177
    AH, I THINK I BROKE MY LEG. 


515
00:39:42,246 --> 00:39:44,547
                HEY.            
                [ Grunting ]    


516
00:39:51,155 --> 00:39:54,690
DON'T WORRY.                    
SOMEBODY'LL FIND US.            
                    [ Grunts ]  


517
00:39:57,362 --> 00:39:59,295
    I'M NOT SO SURE.            


518
00:39:59,363 --> 00:40:02,297
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?            
THERE'S A CHANCE THAT           
NOBODY KNOWS WE'RE OUT HERE?    


519
00:40:02,366 --> 00:40:07,136
    I DON'T KNOW.               
    I DON'T KNOW IF THE MAYDAY  
    TRANSMISSION MADE IT OUT.   


520
00:40:07,205 --> 00:40:10,372
[ Sighs ]                       
WELL, WHAT THE HELL             
DO YOU SUGGEST WE DO?           


521
00:40:11,876 --> 00:40:14,743
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>THERE'S ABOUT SIX OR</i>            
<i>SEVEN HOURS LEFT OF SUNLIGHT.</i>   


522
00:40:14,813 --> 00:40:18,113
        IF YOU TRAVEL LIGHTLY,  
        YOU CAN MAKE IT         
        TO FORT HANCOCK BY DARK.


523
00:40:18,182 --> 00:40:21,150
- ME? WHAT IF I DON'T MAKE IT?  
- YOU'LL MAKE IT.               


524
00:40:21,219 --> 00:40:24,621
    [ Sighs ]                   
                <i> HEAD DUE SOUTH.</i>


525
00:40:25,790 --> 00:40:28,957
            AND HERE'S A FULL   
            CANTEEN OF WATER.   


526
00:40:29,026 --> 00:40:31,494
            <i> MAKE SURE YOU DRINK</i>
            <i> PLENTY OF IT.</i>      


527
00:40:31,562 --> 00:40:33,662
        <i> YOU WOULDN'T WANT TO</i>   
        <i> END UP LIKE TOM.</i>       


528
00:40:37,669 --> 00:40:39,602
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.              


529
00:40:39,671 --> 00:40:42,238
            COUNT ON IT.        


530
00:41:23,381 --> 00:41:26,315
<i>[ Voice Whispering ]</i>            
<i>CAROL.</i>                          


531
00:41:32,523 --> 00:41:36,392
<i>[ Chanting ]</i>                    


532
00:41:49,273 --> 00:41:52,474
    -<i> [ Voice Whispering ]</i>      
     <i> CAROL.</i>                    
    - [ Echoing ] WHO'S THERE?  


533
00:42:04,222 --> 00:42:06,222
        [ Gasps ]               


534
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:08,190
<i>[ Voice Whispering ]</i>            
<i>CAROL.</i>                          


535
00:42:11,062 --> 00:42:13,262
    WHAT'S HAPPENING TO ME?     


536
00:42:13,330 --> 00:42:15,364
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>SAME THING THAT HAPPENED</i>        
<i>TO TOM MILES.</i>                   


537
00:42:17,936 --> 00:42:22,638
- TOM?                          
- NOW, MAYBE YOU CAN IMAGINE HOW
  TOM FELT THOSE LAST MOMENTS.  


538
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:25,208
<i>DYING OUT HERE, ALL ALONE.</i>      


539
00:42:29,414 --> 00:42:32,681
<i>TOM. TOM, I'M SORRY.</i>            


540
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:37,386
        <i> YOU TOOK HIS CANTEEN,</i>  
        <i> AND YOU POISONED IT</i>    
        <i> WITH BELLADONNA.</i>       


541
00:42:39,290 --> 00:42:43,826
<i>THE HARDER THE SUN BORE DOWN,</i>   
<i>THE MORE DELIRIOUS HE BECAME</i>    
<i>WITH EVERY TAINTED DRINK.</i>       


542
00:42:43,895 --> 00:42:47,596
<i>AND EVERY MINUTE THAT PASSED WAS</i>
<i>JUST ANOTHER AGONIZING MOMENT...</i>


543
00:42:47,665 --> 00:42:51,367
        WHEN HE REALIZED HE     
        WOULD NEVER SEE HIS BABY
        THAT HE WANTED SO MUCH. 


544
00:42:51,436 --> 00:42:54,603
        <i> IT GOT SO BAD THAT</i>     
        <i> HE WANDERED IN CIRCLES.</i>


545
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:58,640
    <i> HE CLAWED AT HIS OWN BODY</i>  
    <i> TO FIGHT OFF THE MADNESS</i>   
    <i> THAT YOU CREATED FOR HIM.</i>  


546
00:42:58,709 --> 00:43:03,246
        <i> [ Echoing ]</i>            
        <i> THE MADNESS THAT</i>       
        <i> YOU CREATED FOR HIM.</i>   


547
00:43:05,216 --> 00:43:07,149
[ Breathing Heavily ]           
NO.                             


548
00:43:07,217 --> 00:43:10,720
IT WAS A SCHOOL                 
AND A FAMILY.                   


549
00:43:10,788 --> 00:43:13,990
<i>YOU TOOK THAT AWAY!</i>             
<i> YOU JUST GAVE IT TO HER!</i>       


550
00:43:14,058 --> 00:43:15,958
    [ Crying ]                  


551
00:43:17,328 --> 00:43:20,762
<i>TILL THERE WAS NOTHING</i>          
<i>LEFT FOR ME.</i>                    


552
00:43:20,831 --> 00:43:24,066
SO YOU LEFT A WIDOW BEHIND AND  
A BABY TO BE BORN FATHERLESS.   


553
00:43:25,703 --> 00:43:27,970
        TOM, I JUST WANTED      
        WHAT I DESERVED.        


554
00:43:30,374 --> 00:43:34,076
    SOMETHING TELLS ME YOU'RE   
    GOING TO GET JUST THAT.     


555
00:44:00,071 --> 00:44:02,170
[ Cell Phone Rings ]            


556
00:44:07,011 --> 00:44:08,944
            HELLO, JAROD.       


557
00:44:09,013 --> 00:44:11,614
    WITH INSTINCTS LIKE THAT,   
    YOU'LL CATCH ME YET.        


558
00:44:11,682 --> 00:44:13,682
    NOT IF YOU KEEP THROWING ME 
    OFF THE TRAIL.              


559
00:44:13,751 --> 00:44:17,787
    OH, I DIDN'T THROW YOU OFF. 
    I JUST PUT YOU              
    ON A DIFFERENT ONE.         


560
00:44:17,855 --> 00:44:21,357
    IS THAT ALL YOU DO, JAROD?  
    DIG UP THE PAST?            


561
00:44:21,425 --> 00:44:25,428
    THAT'S EASY FOR YOU TO SAY. 
    YOU<i> HAVE</i> ONE.               


562
00:44:25,496 --> 00:44:28,263
ALTHOUGH, IT'S NOT QUITE        
WHAT YOU THOUGHT IT WAS, IS IT? 


563
00:44:30,568 --> 00:44:32,501
            HAPPY BIRTHDAY.     


564
00:44:39,110 --> 00:44:40,876
<i>[ Angela ]</i>                      
<i>OKAY, SWEETIE.</i>                  
<i>LET'S GO NIGHT-NIGHT.</i>           


565
00:44:57,027 --> 00:44:59,161
                [ Fussing ]     


566
00:45:07,105 --> 00:45:09,905
HO, WHITE MAN.                  


567
00:45:09,974 --> 00:45:13,342
        CAME BY TO SAY GOOD-BYE,
        THANK YOU.              


568
00:45:15,046 --> 00:45:18,447
WELL, SO LONG,                  
AND YOU'RE WELCOME.             


569
00:45:20,218 --> 00:45:24,120
    WHEN WE FIRST MET, YOU      
    TOLD ME YOU WERE GONNA      
    HELP ME DISCOVER THE TRUTH. 


570
00:45:25,723 --> 00:45:29,825
            I WAS KIND OF HOPING
            IT WOULD HAVE BEEN  
            ABOUT MYSELF.       


571
00:45:30,961 --> 00:45:32,895
            ABOUT WHO I AM.     


572
00:45:34,031 --> 00:45:37,732
WE EACH TAKE A JOURNEY          
WE'RE MEANT TO TAKE.            


573
00:45:37,801 --> 00:45:41,971
FOR SOME, IT'S CLEAR.           
 FOR OTHERS, NOT SO CLEAR.      


574
00:45:45,509 --> 00:45:47,442
    AM I GOING THE RIGHT WAY?   


575
00:45:49,714 --> 00:45:52,114
    JUST KEEP LISTENING         
    TO YOUR GUT.                


576
00:45:52,182 --> 00:45:54,116
[ Wind Blows ]                  


577
00:46:38,863 --> 00:46:39,862
            [ Mews ]            


